is a Japanese manga series written by Tsuina Miura and illustrated by Takahiro Oba. The series was serialized online in DeNA's Manga Box app from December 2013 to April 2019, with Kodansha compiling it into twenty-one  volumes. The manga is licensed in North America by Seven Seas Entertainment. A sequel manga titled  was serialized in Kodansha's Magazine Pocket website and app from July 2019 to April 2021, with seven  volumes released.
An original net animation (ONA) series adaptation produced by Zero-G streamed worldwide on Netflix in February 2021.
Premise
High school girl Yuri Honjō is transported to a world full of skyscrapers and suspension bridges connecting them. She then finds herself being hunted by mysterious figures wearing masks. She later discovers that her brother, Rika, is also trapped in this world. She thereupon encounters other teenagers in the same situation, but it is not clear if they will be friends or foes.
Characters
